By James Samuel , Minna Abuja (Sundiata Post) – The Honorable Commissioner Ministry for Local Government, Chieftaincy Affairs and Internal Security, Niger State, Hon. Emmanuel Umar has felicitates with Emir of Minna, HRH. Alh. Dr. Umar Faruq Bahago on his 64th birthday. Mr Emmanuel while felicitates with the Emir pray that Almighty Allah continue to grant His Royal Highness many more years of service to the people of the Emirate. “As you mark your 64th birthday anniversary and 34th years on the throne, Your Highness, your leadership qualities are evident of faith in the peace, unity, progress, and prosperity of our dear Emirate and has also make you one of the most highly respected monarchs in Nigeria today.” “As you continue to use your exalted throne to build bridges of friendship and harmony across the state and beyond; it is my prayer that Almighty God grants you many more years of abounding health, prosperity and enduring fulfillment. By Chibuike Nwabuko Abuja (Sundiata Post) - Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Dr. Isa Ali Ibrahim Pantami and the Executive Vice Chairman of the Nigerian Communications Commission (NCC), Prof. Umar Garba Danbatta, have felicitated with Alhaji Aminu Ado Beyero on his coronation as the 15th Emir of Kano. The… In "Top Stories" ABUJA - President Goodluck Jonathan has expressed appreciation to the Alaafin of Oyo, Oba Lamidi Adeyemi III, for his continued support to the Federal Government’s efforts at accelerating the country’s socio-economic development. This is contained in a statement issued by the Special Adviser to the President on Media and Publicity,… In "News" By Naomi Sharang Abuja -  Senate President Bukola Saraki, on Saturday congratulated the Emir of Ilorin, Alhaji Ibrahim Sulu-Gambari on attaining 22 years on the throne of his forebears. Saraki in a statement by his Special Adviser, Media and Publicity, Mr Yusuph Olaniyonu, described the emir as an exceptional royal… In "Top Stories"